      • containsAll

        public static <T> boolean containsAll​(T[] a,
                                      T[] b)
        compres a set of terms (assumed to be unique) with another set to find if their contents match. they can be in different order and still match. this is useful for comparing whether compound terms in which order doesn't matter (ex: conjunction) are equivalent.
